<tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><img border="0" src="../triangle.JPG"><font size="3" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>STAFF OF THE SERPENT (EPIC QUEST)</b></font></p></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Class:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>Enchanter</b></font></td></tr> <tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Minimum Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">50</font></td></tr> <tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Estimated Quest Length:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Over 30 hours</font></td></tr> <tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Quest NPC:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Stofo Olan</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Starting Zone:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Erudin, Palace&Comment=1">Erudin, Palace</a></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Secondary Zones:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Ak Anon&Comment=1">Ak Anon</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Qeynos, South&Comment=1">Qeynos, South</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Karana, West&Comment=1">Karana, West</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Burning Woods&Comment=1">Burning Woods</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Cabilis, East&Comment=1">Cabilis, East</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Overthere&Comment=1">Overthere</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Neriak, Third Gate&Comment=1">Neriak, Third Gate</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Chardok&Comment=1">Chardok</a></font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><a href="../zones/zoneinfo.asp?Zone=Felwithe, South&Comment=1">Felwithe, South</a></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Items Needed:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Mechanical Pen, Ink of the Dark, White Paper</font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Copy of Notes</font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Jeb's Seal</font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Enchanter's Bag</font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Xolion Rod, Innoruuk's Word, Chalice of Kings</font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Spoon, One Key, Lost Scroll, Charm and Sacrifice</font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Enchanted Diamond,  Sapphire, Ruby, and Emerald</font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Head of a Serpent, Essence of a Ghost</font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Essence of a Vampire, Sands of the Mystics</font></p><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">1st, 2nd, 3rd, and 4th Piece of Staff</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Description:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>1.</b> The first thing you should do is search <b>Stofo Olan</b>.  You can find him on the 2nd floor of the Vasty Deep Inn across Erudin's City Library, at loc -1100 -60.  Hail him and the conversation is as follows:
<br><br>
<i>'Good day, I have discovered something truly wonderful! If I only had the materials required so I can copy my notes and send them to my teacher'</i>.
<br>
Ask him 'What materials'
<br>
<i>'The materials I need are a mechanical pen, ink of the dark, and white paper. Bring me those and I will give you a copy of this information'</i>.
Ask him 'Who is your teacher'
<i>'My teacher is Jeb Lumsed. He was last seen in the regions of the newly discovered lands. If you wish to find him that is where you must seek him out'</i>
<br><br>
<b>2.</b> So you need to gather three different items and bring them back to Stofo Olan, a Mechanical Pen, Ink of the Dark, and White Paper.
<br><br>
<b>3.</b> You can find the <b>Mechanical Pen</b> in Ak'Anon.  Look for <b>Rilgor Plegnog</b> in the Mines of Malfunction in Ak Anon.  Once you find him, ask him about the Mechanical Pen.  He will say the following: <i>'Why do you want one of those contraptions. You will spend more time repairing it then you will writing with it. But if you insist on getting one, you are going to have to do a small favor.'  Rilgor Plegnog tugs at your robe and grins evilly. Mighty nice outfit you have there. Sure beats these drab robes us three are wearing. Hmm...my favorite color is purple, in fact a shiny metallic purple would do nicely. How bad did you want that pen?'</i>.  He is talking about a <b>Shining Metallic Robe</b>.  (Note: this part might work with a different robe, it is unknown at this point).  Hand him the Shining Metallic Robe and in return he will give you the Mechanical Pen.
<br><br>
<b>4.</b> To obtain the <b>Ink of the Dark</b>, you must go to Qeynos.  Look for <b>Reania Jukle</b>, the Enchanter guildmaster in the Temple under Qeynos, at loc +2030 -580.  Ask Reania about the Ink of the Dark and then ask her where you can find the Ink of the Dark.  She will say the following: <i>'The ink is the blood of a dark scribe. Tempt him and give him this vial. He should cooperate'</i>.  She will also give you an <b>Empty Ink Vial</b>.
<br><br>
<b>5.</b> Head to Lower Guk and go to the Ghoul Sage Room.  A <b>Ghoul Scribe</b>, a level 35 Enchanter with 1400 HPs, spawns in this same room, and has a Wan Knight as his placeholder.  The loc for this room is +540 -710.  Charm the Ghoul Scribe and hand him the Empty Ink Vial.  He will return you the <b>Ink of the Dark</b>.
<br><br>
<b>6.</b> The last piece of this section of the quest is obtaining the <b>White Paper</b>.  To get it, you must go to the West Karana, but before you do so, make sure you bring a paper and a quill with you.  Now head to West Karana and look for <b>Chrislin Baker</b>.  Chrislin is a level 45 Human Shopkeeper that spawns at loc +1050 -1990.  Talk to her and she will ask you for some writing materials since the ones she had were stolen.  Give her the paper and quill and she will say the following: <i>Chrislin Baker gives you a hug. 'Thank you so much. I did some cleaning after you left and found this behind a barrel. It may have been left behind by the person who took my materials. You can have it'</i>.  She will then give you a <b>Bandit Sash</b>.
<br><br>
<b>7.</b> A Human Monk named <b>Thrackin Griffen</b> will now spawn at loc +880 -11570.  Kill him and you and loot the <b>White Paper</b>.
<br><br>
<b>8.</b> You now have the 3 items Stofo asked for, the Mechanical Pen, Ink of the Dark, and White Paper.  Head back to Erudin and look for Stofo.  Give him the three items and he will say the following: 'Yes, that is what I wanted. Here, take these notes. <i>'My teacher will be very interested if he knows what I have found'</i>.  He will then give you a <b>Copy of Notes</b>.
<br><br>
<b>9.</b> When you first spoke to Stofo, he mentions that his teacher is <b>Jeb Lumsed</b>.  You can find him in the Burning Woods.  Once you are there, look for a <b>Sarnak Imitator</b>.  He is an Enchanter, usually with a pet, that is actually Jeb Lumsed.  Once you find the Sarnak, ask if he is Jeb and should say he is.  Give him the Copy of Notes and he will say the following:
<br><br>
<i>'I see that you have what I was waiting for. Stofo does do excellent work. It seems that you are to start on a long journey. Take this seal and it will guide you on your next step. Seek out the masters of enchantment. In time we will craft the Serpent for you. When you have collected the four parts of the staff, you must combine them in a bundle for me. If you need a sack, just let me know'</i>.  He will also give you the coin <b>Jeb's Seal</b>.
<br><br>
Tell him 'I need a sack'
<br>
<i>'Take this sack and combine the items I requested in it. Then return it to me'</i>.  He will then give you an <b>Enchanter's Bag</b>.
<br><br>
Ask him 'Who are the four other masters'
<br>
<i>'The masters are enchanters who have reached the plateau of understanding. Their names are Modani Qu'Loni, Mizzle Gepple, Nadia Starfeast, and Polzin Mrid. All are master crafters in their own right'</i>.
<br><br>
Ask him 'Who is Modani'
<br>
<i>'Modani is a master of illusions. You should seek him out first. Keep a careful eye out for him - he is never in his true form. The last time I spoke to him, he seemed very excited about his voyage to the elven outpost. You may or may not find more clues about his location there'</i>.
<br><br>
Ask him 'Who is Mizzle'
<br>
<i>'Mizzle is a gnome who has mastered the use of enlightened magic. Go to him once you have spoken to Modani. Mizzle is not one to travel, so you should not have to look far from his home to find him'</i>.
<br><br>
Ask him 'Who is Nadia'
<br>
<i>'The mistress of charm, Nadia is very beautiful. She, too, traveled with her relatives to the new land. I just recently received a letter from her. She says more and more pilgrims and explorers are arriving every day, and that the outpost is well defended now'</i>.
<br><br>
Ask him 'Who is Polzin'
<br>
<i>'Master of the Phantasms - he is the last one you will seek out. Hmm...Polzin is native to Erudin, however, after the incident near Paineel, no one has heard from him. I hope that he is well'</i>.
<br><br>
<b>10.</b> You must now seek the four masters mentioned above and collect a variety of different items.
<br><br>
<b>11.</b> The first one you should seek out is <b>Modani Qu'Loni</b> in Overthere, at loc +540 -940.  Modani is a spider/lizard.  Hail him and ask for a sack.  Modani will then give you another <b>Enchanter's Bag</b> and ask you to collect four different items, the Xolion Rod, Innoruuk's Word, Chalice of Kings, and Snow Blossoms.
<br><br>
<b>12.</b> The <b>Xolion Rod</b> can be obtained by killing <b>Vessel Drozlin</b> in the Cabilis Shaman guild at loc +590 -830.  Kill Drozlin and loot the Xolion Rod.
<br><br>
<b>13.</b> Next you must go to Neriak 3rd Gate.  Inside the Cleric guild you will find <b>Verina Tomb</b>.  If she is not there, well, you will have to wait or come back later.  Verina is on a 48-hour spawn.  Once she does spawn, you must kill her.  She is a level 60 Dark Elf Cleric with no faction ties.  This means you can kill her and other NPCs will not interfere.  Kill her and loot <b>Innoruuk's Word</b>.
<br><br>
<b>14.</b> The third item you have to obtain is the <b>Chalice of Kings</b>.  To get it, you must first go to Chardok and look for <b>Prince Selrach Di'zok</b>.  The Prince is close to the Overking room, deep inside Chardok, at loc -560 +1360.  The Prince is a level 61 Sarnak Warrior and to fight him and clear the path to his room you will need at least 3 groups.  Kill the Prince and loot the <b>Prince's Head</b>.
<br><br>
<b>15.</b> Now that you have the Prince's Head, go to Felwithe and look for the <b>Joren Nobleheart</b> in the Magician guild.  Talk to him and he will ask for the Prince's Head.  Give it to him and he will say the following: <i>'Vengeance has been fufilled! However, the King still has a heavy heart. Not until Firiona has been return can this sadness be lifted. But in appreciation of your efforts, I am honored to present to you the King's Chalice'</i>.  He will then give you the Chalice of Kings.
<br><br>
<b>16.</b> The fourth and final item you need to obtain for Modani are the <b>Snow Blossoms</b>.  Head to Oggok and look for <b>Bozlum Blossom</b> at loc +540 +1150.  Hail her and she will proceed to tell you the following:
<br><br>
<i>Bozlum Blossom heaves a great sigh.</i>
<br><br>
Ask her 'What is wrong Bozlum?'
<br>
<i>'Boz like to grow perty flowers in her garden. But garden no more'</i>.
<br><br>
Ask her 'What happened to your perty flower garden?'
<i>''Boz not know what happen. Only see der biggins footprints in it. Me perty sure my puppy not smash garden. He has tiny feets. Right, puppy?'. Bozlum Blossom pet wags his tail</i>.
<br><br>
Her puppy is a dog standing right next to her.
<br><br>
<b>17.</b> Now look for <b>Brokk Boxtripper</b> at loc +230 +380.  Once you find him, look for a pair of sandals right next to him.  Get it and you will see they are called <b>Large Muddy Sandals</b>.
<br><br>
<b>18.</b> Take the sandals back to Bozlum and give it to her.  She will then give you a <b>Scribbled Parchment</b> and ask that you take it to Brokk.
<br><br>
<b>19.</b> Go to Brokk and give him the Parchment.  He will apologize for messing with Bozlum's garden and give you a <b>Gift to Bozlum</b> so you can take it to Bozlum.
<br><br>
<b>20.</b> Find Bozlum and give her the Gift.  She will say the following: <i>'Oh, dat silly Brokk. He sent me too many of these perty flowers. Me not know where put them all. Here, you take some cause you help Bozlum. Me like you. Flowers make you smell perty, too'</i>.  She will then give you the Snow Blossoms.
<br><br>
<b>21.</b> Once you have the 4 items, Xolion Rod, Innoruuk's Word, the Chalice of Kings, and Snow Blossoms, put all 4 of them in the Enchanter's Bag Modani previously gave you and hit the combine button.  You will create a new item called a <b>Sack for Modani</b>.
<br><br>
<b>22.</b> As you might have imagined, you must go back to Overthere and look for Modani once again.  Give him the Sack for Modani and he will say the following: <i>'Excellent, you have done well. Here is the first piece of the staff. Now you must go seek out the second master; he will clear the path for you'</i>.  He will then give you the <b>1st Piece of Staff</b>.
<br><br>
<b>23.</b> You must now seek out the second master, <b>Mizzle Gepple</b> in the Mines of Malfunction in Ak'Anon, at loc +2020 -520.  Mizzle is actually a Clockwork.  You will see him as <b>Clockwork VIIX</b>.  Ask him if he is Mizzle and should say he is.  Ask for a sack.  Mizzle will then give you another <b>Enchanter's Bag</b> and ask you to collect four different items, a Spoon, the One Key, the Lost Scroll, and the book Charm and Sacrifice.
<br><br>
<b>24.</b> To find the <b>Spoon</b>, you must go to the Oasis of Marr.  A Sand Giant called <b>Cazel</b> can be found here.  Cazel is a rare spawn and is level 50.  He hits very hard and can remain invulnerable for at least 1 minute. 2 groups are recommended to kill Cazel.  Kill him and loot the Spoon.
<br><br>
<b>25.</b> The next item you need to obtain is the <b>One Key</b>.  To get it, you must head to Overthere and look on top of a tiny mesa at loc -190 -380.  Is the key is not there, you will have to wait a little.  The key spawns every 24 hours.  Pick it up once it spawns.
<br><br>
<b>26.</b> The way you obtain the next item, the <b>Lost Scroll</b> is similar to that of the One Key.  Head to Dalnir's Crypt and go to loc -20 +50.  You will see a bed next to a wall.  The scroll will spawn between the bed and the wall every 24 hours.  Pick it up once it spawns.
<br><br>
<b>27.</b> The same is true for the book <b>Charm and Sacrifice</b>.  You can find it in the Plane of Sky, on the right table near an Efreeti spawn at loc +1300 +560.  The book spawns every 24 hours.  Pick it up once it spawns.
<br><br>
<b>28.</b> You now have the 4 items you set you to collect, the Spoon, the One Key, the Lost Scroll, and the book Charm and Sacrifice.  Put all 4 of them in the Enchanter's Bag Mizzle previously gave you and hit the combine button.  You will create a new item called a <b>Sack for Mizzle</b>.
<br><br>
<b>29.</b> Now go back to Ak'Anon and look for Mizzle once again.  Give him the Sack for Mizzle and he will say the following: <i>'Oh excellent, you have done what is required. Here take this part, and seek the third master, you are well on your way'</i>.  He will then give you the <b>2nd Piece of Staff</b>.
<br><br>
<b>30.</b> You are now ready to look for the third master, <b>Nadia Starfeast</b> inside a little hut in Firiona Vie, at loc -3870 +2525.  Hail her and ask for a sack.  Nadia will then give you another <b>Enchanter's Bag</b> and ask that you to obtain the essence of four different precious stones, a Dull Diamond, a Dull Sapphire, a Dull Ruby, and a Dull Emerald.
<br><br>
<b>31.</b> To obtain the essence of these gems, you will need to transform them into enchanted versions of the gems.  To do so, you will need to charm a few different creatures.
<br><br>
<b>32.</b> To obtain the <b>Enchanted Diamond</b>, you need to go to Kaesora.  Enter Kaesora and levitate your party.  Now go straight ahead and drop down the hole and keep moving forward.  You will walk onto a ledge and reach the 2nd floor.  Enter the spider room and go through the door to your right.  A fake wall is behind that door.  Go through it and follow the passage down until you get to the large building.  Inside it, you will find a <b>Spectral Librarian</b> or a <b>Tortured Librarian</b> (loc +85 -415 +100).  The one you are looking for is the Spectral Librarian, so if he is not there, kill the Tortured Librarian until the Spectral Librarian spawns.  Once he does, charm him and give him the Dull Diamond.  He will then give you the Enchanted Diamond and turn into a Enraged Spectral Librarian.  It is not needed, but you can kill this spawn and it will turn into three Freed Souls, each with only 1 hitpoint.
<br><br>
<b>33.</b> Now head to Skyfire and look for the little Chromodac called <b>Felia Goldenwing</b> at loc +1550 -1000, near the Burning Woods zone.  Felia is an uncommon spawn and you might have to kill other uncommon spawns to trigger her spawn.  Once she does spawn, quickly charm her and avoid taking her anywhere near other Skyfire spawns.  Other mobs will kill her on sight.  After you charm Felia, hand her the Dull Sapphire and she will give you an <b>Enchanted Sapphire</b>.
<br><br>
<b>34.</b> Head to the City of Mist and look for the <b>Wraith of Jaxion</b>.  It spawns in Neh'Ashiir's building at loc +15 +20.  The Wraith of Jaxion is an uncommon spawn.  If it is not there, keep killing everything inside the building until it spawns.  Once it does, charm it and hand the Dull Ruby.  In return, you will obtain the <b>Enchanted Ruby</b>.
<br><br>
<b>35.</b> Finally, for the last gem you need to go to Overthere.  Look for a spider/lizard called <b>Impaler Tzilug</b> inside a building at loc -90 +810.  Charm the Impaler (you might have to kill its guardians to achieve this) and give him the Dull Emerald.  In return, he will give you the <b>Enchanted Emerald</b>.
<br><br>
<b>36.</b> That completes the set of 4 enchanted gems, the Enchanted Diamond, Enchanted Sapphire, Enchanted Ruby, and Enchanted Emerald.  Put all 4 of them in the Enchanter's Bag Nadia previously gave you and hit the combine button.  You will create a new item called a <b>Sack for Nadia</b>.
<br><br>
<b>37.</b> Now go back to Firiona Vie and look for Nadia once again.  Give her the Sack for Nadia and she will say the following: <i>'Excellent, you have done what is required. Here take this part, and seek the fourth master, to complete your quest'</i>.  She will then give you the <b>3rd Piece of Staff</b>.
<br><br>
<b>38.</b> It is now time to meet the last master, <b>Polzin Mrid</b>.  You can find him in the back of one of the shops in the Elemental city in The Hole.  Hail him and give him <b>Jeb's Seal</b>.  Now tell him you are ready for the Test of the Phantasm and then ask him for a sack.  He will give you an <b>Enchanter's Bag</b> and ask you for four different items, Head of a Serpent, Essence of a Ghost, Essence of a Vampire, and Sands of the Mystics.
<br><br>
<b>39.</b> You should get the <b>Essence of a Ghost</b> first since it is found in your current zone, The Hole.  You must look for <b>the Ghost of Kindle</b>, a spawn in between the city and Master Yael's lair.  Kill her and loot the Essence of a Ghost.
<br><br>
<b>40.</b> The <b>Head of a Serpent</b> is found in the Plane of Fear.  Head over there with a few groups and make your way to <b>Cazic Thule</b>.  Kill Cazic and soon after a <b>Shissar Spirit</b> will spawn.  Kill it and loot the Head of the Serpent.
<br><br>
<b>41.</b> The <b>Essence of a Vampire</b> is found in the Plane of Hate.  They are dropped by <b>Forsaken Revenants</b>, level 49 to 51 Magician or Enchanter mobs.  Keep killing them until you obtain the Essence of a Vampire.
<br><br>
<b>42.</b> Finally, the last item you need to obtain is the <b>Sands of the Mystics</b>.  Head to the Field of Bone and look for the uncommon spawn named <b>The Tangrin</b>.  He is a level 54 Gorilla Warrior with over 32,000 HPs.  He spawns at loc +3300 +2530 and then proceeds to walk around not too far from that point.  Kill The Tangrin and loot your final item, the Sands of the Mystics.
<br><br>
<b>43.</b> You now have the 4 items you set out to obtain, the Head of a Serpent, Essence of a Ghost, Essence of a Vampire, and Sands of the Mystics.  Put all 4 of them in the Enchanter's Bag Polzin previously gave you and hit the combine button.  You will create a new item called a <b>Sack for Polzin</b>.
<br><br>
<b>44.</b> Now go back to The Hole and look for Polzin.  Give him the Sack for Polzin and he will say the following: <i>'Excellent, you have done what is required. Here take this part, and return to Master Jeb Lumsed'</i>.  He will then give you the <b>4th Piece of Staff</b>.
<br><br>
<b>45.</b> You are almost done with the quest.  Return to Burning Woods and look for <b>Jeb Lumsed</b>.  Remember, he is disguised as a Sarnak Imitator at loc -1200 -4000.  Find him and make sure you have an <b>Enchanter's Bag</b>.  He gave you one before but if you don't have it for some reason, ask for a sack once again.  Now put all four <b>Pieces of Staff</b> in your Enchanter's Bag and hit the combine button.  Yoou will create a new item called <b>Bundle of Staves</b>.
<br><br>
<b>46.</b> Give the Bundle of Staves to Jeb Lumsed and he will say the following: <i>'The path you trod was long and hard. Now you are worthy to bear the Serpent. Use it well'</i>.  He will then give you the Staff of the Serpent.</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Author:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Wraith (Bristlebane)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Quest Reward:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>Staff of the Serpent</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma"></font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>STR+5  STA+15  CHA+15  INT+15  HP+40  Mana+40  SV Fire+10  SV Disease+10  SV Cold+10  SV Magic+10  SV Poison+10   Effect: Speed of the Shissar</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rating:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>8.7</b> (average of <b>42</b> votes)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rate this quest:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" a